      "id": 547,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:3",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "content": "DONE — three light-mode CSS bugs fixed in `public/index.html`. No commit per instructions.\n\n**Changes made (6 CSS lines changed/added):**\n\n**1. Text contrast — unselected messages now muted**\n- `.message-content`: changed `color: var(--text)` → `color: var(--muted)`\n- Added `.message-row:hover .message-content, .message-row.from-human .message-content { color: var(--text); }` — lifts to full text color on hover or for human messages\n\n**2. Hover feedback — background-based, not brightness filter**\n- Replaced `.message-row:hover { filter: brightness(1.15); }` (the root cause — lightens in light mode) with:\n  - `.message-row:hover { background: var(--hover); transition: background 120ms; }`\n  - `.message-row.p0:hover { background: var(--p0-hover-bg); }`\n- Added `--hover` to both themes: `rgba(0,0,0,0.045)` (light) and `rgba(255,255,255,0.045)` (dark) — ~4.5% tint, subtle but visible\n- Added `--p0-hover-bg`: `#fee2e2` (light, deeper red wash) and `#3a1616` (dark, deeper red wash)\n\n**3. P0 hover now increases emphasis**\n- Changed `.from-agent.p0 .message-content { color: #fca5a5; }` → `color: var(--p0)` (works correctly in both themes — red in dark, stronger red in light)\n- Added `.message-row.p0:hover .message-content { color: var(--p0); }` so hover doesn't accidentally inherit the lifted `--text` color\n\n**Hover feel summary:**\n- Normal agent messages: text lifts from muted grey → full text color; background gets subtle 4.5% tint\n- Human messages: always full text color (prominent sender); same subtle bg on hover\n- P0 messages: background deepens to a richer red wash on hover — MORE prominent, not less",
